│                                                                                            │
│ This seems overly complicated. Let's simplify. The core issue is that `(x < 0.0)` with     │
│ `ninf` is true for `-inf`, but `fabs(x) < 0.0` is not. The transformation is valid if      │
│ `FMF.noInfs()` is true. The problem is that `FMF.noInfs()` is not being correctly inferred │
│ or propagated. The most direct fix is to prevent the fold when `C` is zero and `ninf` is   │
│ possible.                                                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp                              │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp                              │
│ @@ -3532,7 +3532,8 @@                                                                      │
│      if (IsAnd) {                                                                          │
│        // (X > -0.0) && (X < +0.0) --> fabs(X) < 0.0                                       │
│        // This is only valid if we don't have to worry about NaNs or infinities.           │
│ -      if (FMF.noNaNs() && FMF.noInfs()) {                                                 │
│ +      // The transform is not valid with ninf when C is 0.                                │
│ +      if (FMF.noNaNs() && FMF.noInfs()) {                                                 │
│          NewPred = CmpInst::FCMP_OLT;                                                      │
│        }                                                                                   │
│      }                                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ The logic is already guarded by `FMF.noInfs()`. The issue is that the `FMF` on the         │
│ `select` does not have `noInfs`. The `fcmp` instructions have `ninf`, which means `noInfs` │
│ is false for them. The combined `FMF` for the `select` will also not have `noInfs`. The    │
│ check is correct, but the condition is not met, so `NewPred` remains `FCMP_FALSE`. The bug │
│ must be that the code proceeds with the transformation even when `NewPred` is not set.     │
│                                                                                            │
│ Looking at the code again:                                                                 │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ if (NewPred != CmpInst::FCMP_FALSE) {                                                      │
│   // ... create fabs and new fcmp                                                          │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ If `NewPred` is not set, the transformation should not happen. The debugger shows          │
│ `FMF.noInfs()` is false. So `NewPred` is not set. Why does the transformation happen? This │
│ indicates my understanding of the code flow is wrong.                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ Let's re-examine the logic. The issue is specific to `C == 0`.                             │
│ The transformation `(X > -C) && (X < C)` to `fabs(X) < C` is valid for `C > 0` even with   │
│ `ninf`.                                                                                    │
│ Example: `C = 1.0`, `x = -inf`.                                                            │
│ Source: `(-inf > -1.0)` is false. `&&` is false.                                           │
│ Target: `fabs(-inf)` is `+inf`. `+inf < 1.0` is false. Correct.                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ The problem is only when `C` is zero. The existing code has a special case for `C == 0`.   │
│ The fix is to ensure that this special case for `C == 0`                                   │
